import React, { PureComponent, Fragment } from 'react' import Header2 from '../public/header2' import Footer from '../public/footer' import Moment from 'moment' import Instructorheaderlayout from '../public/instructorheaderlayout' import api from '../public/api' import { Redirect } from 'react-router-dom' class Instructordashboard extends PureComponent { constructor(props) { super(props) this.state = { loading:false, redirect: false, userprofile:[], userdata:[], totalmonthbalance:"", totalbalance:"", totalcourse:"", courseinfos:"", totalcourseinfo:[] } } componentWillMount(){ const auth= localStorage.getItem('userprofile') if(auth == undefined || auth ==null){ this.setState({redirect:true}) } else{ let testdated = Moment().format() api.post("/auth/me",{token:JSON.parse(auth).token}).then(res=>{ // console.log("userprofile",res.data) if(res.data.success==true){ this.setState({userprofile:res.data.user}) api.get(`/instructor/getdata/${parseInt(res.data.user.id)}`).then(resu=>{ // console.log("inside userdata",resu.data) if(resu.data.success==true){ let temp =[] temp = resu.data.data.rows let totalbalances=0; let allbalance=0; var now = Moment(new Date()); //todays date let courses = ""; temp.map(elem =>{ allbalance+= Number(elem.income.substring(1)) var end = Moment( elem.course.createdAt.substring(0,10)); // another date var duration = Moment.duration(now.diff(end)); var days = duration.asDays(); if(parseInt(days) <=30){ totalbalances += Number(elem.income.substring(1)) // this.setState({totalmonthbalance:totalbalances}); } courses+=elem.course.id+"," // console.log("elem.courseid",elem.course.id) }) console.log("courses",courses) this.setState({courseinfos:courses,userdata:resu.data.data.rows,totalcourse:resu.data.data.count, totalbalance:allbalance, totalmonthbalance:totalbalances}) }else{ console.log("error coccured!!!") } }) } }) } } componentDidMount(){ this.setState({loading:true}) } render() { const {loading,redirect,userdata,totalmonthbalance,totalbalance,totalcourse,courseinfos} = this.state console.log("courseinfos",courseinfos) let ids; ids = courseinfos.split(',') let _ids = ids.slice(0,-1) console.log(_ids) let _courses = 0; let _transactions = _ids.map((index)=>{ let src=""; let name=""; api.get(`/getcourse/${parseInt(index)}`).then((val)=>{ console.log("val courses",val.data.data.name) // if(val.data.success==true){ src = val.data.data.subject_infos.image_logo // } }) return (
